thread.title: Shawnee upsets Tipp as QB Bennett returns
thread.title_full: Shawnee upsets Tipp as QB Bennett returns

title: Shawnee upsets Tipp as QB Bennett returns
text:
Posted: 6:12 p.m. Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015 Shawnee upsets Tipp as QB Bennett returns By Staff Staff Writer 
Welcome back, Alec Bennett. 
The Shawnee senior quarterback, playing his first game since breaking his collarbone during the preseason, led an upset of undefeated Tippecanoe 35-28 late Friday night. 
The Braves scored the winning touchdown with 1:30 left in the fourth quarter, a drive kept alive by a conversion on fourth-and-8 at the Tipp 43-yard line with just under two minutes left. 
On fourth down, Bennett scrambled and saw receiver Michael Guyer open near the end zone. Guyer hauled in the pass at the 1-yard line. T.J. King scored on the next play. 
Bennett, who also had a 42-yard touchdown run, completed 16-of-28 passes for 188 yards. 
Shawnee also received a boost from the return of linebacker Ta’Von Kerby. Running back Josh Nelson and backup quarterback Will Finch have also returned in a season where the Braves have been decimated by injuries, including injuries to four quarterbacks 
Shawnee racked up 18 first downs to five for Tipp and held an offensive advantage in yards at 375 to 271. 
Shawnee improved to 2-3 overall and 1-0 in the Central Buckeye Conference Kenton Division. Tipp fell to 5-1 and 0-1 CBC Kenton. 
Greeneview 37, Catholic Central 14: Logan Test rushed for 192 yards and three TDs as the Rams (4-2, 2-1 Ohio Heritage Conference) opened with 17 points in the first quarter. Jacob Green led the defense with seven tackles and a 14-yard interception return for a touchdown. 
Jake Guiterrez led Catholic Central (3-3, 1-2 OHC) with 11 tackles. 
Ben Logan 38, Northwestern 3: The Warriors (3-3, 0-1 Mad River CBC) trailed 17-3 after three quarters, but couldn’t get closer as the Raiders (3-3, 1-0 Mad River CBC) put it away with three fourth-quarter touchdowns. 
Urbana 59, Greenon 6: Nick Johnson rushed for 174 yards and three TDs on 17 carries to lead the Hillclimbers (2-4, 1-0 CBC Mad River). Levi Boettcher completed 7-of-10 passes for 179 yards and two TDs, both to Alex Lohnes for 69 and 41 yards. Greenon fell to 0-6 and 0-1 Mad River CBC. 
Northeastern 15, Southeastern 9: The Jets grabbed their first win to improve to 1-5 overall and 1-3 OHC. Southeastern dropped to 2-4 and 2-1 OHC. 
Indian Lake 47, Graham 0: The Lakers (4-2, 1-0 CBC Mad River) handed Graham (1-5, 0-1 CBC Mad River) its second shutout this season. 
Triad 39, Cedarville 7: Trent McIntyre threw for three touchdowns and ran for another to lift the Cardinals to 2-4 overall and 1-2 in the OHC. Cedarville (1-5, 0-3 OHC) was held to 14 yards in total offense. More News
